      "message": "tl;dr AsSelf is most likely wrong here.\n\nWe shouldn\u0027t use this in new services. It is susceptible to the confused deputy problem: while working in project A, I can abuse ResultDB to do something to resources of project B (for example, read otherwise hidden from me results). \n\nThis should be either AsUser or AsProject. What this client is used for exactly (what incoming RPCs)? Are they happening in a context of some LUCI project? (If not, they probably should).\n\nNote that this is mostly unrelated to \"realms\" or \"buckets\" or whatever: even if we have fancier authorization  model for incoming requests, we still must not use AsSelf for outgoing requests happening in a context of a concrete project (or realm or bucket or whatever, but currently projects are the boundary).",
